  "prompt": "What are some books or videos for understanding how the Indian economy works?",
  "response": "Here are some recommended resources for understanding the Indian economy:\n\nBooks:\n1. \"India's Economy: From Socialism to Market Economy\" by Dwijendra Tripathi\n2. \"Transforming the Indian Economy\" by Rakesh Mohan\n3. \"India's Economic Reforms and Development\" by Isher Judge Ahluwalia\n4. \"The Oxford Handbook of the Indian Economy\" edited by Kirit Parikh\n5. \"India's Long Road\" by Christophe Jaffrelot and Rahul Mukherji\n\nAcademic Videos/Lectures:\n1. NDTV Economics Lectures\n2. Lectures by Raghuram Rajan (former RBI Governor)\n3. Harvard Business School's India-focused economic lectures\n4. World Bank and IMF lecture series on Indian economy\n\nOnline Courses:\n1. Coursera - Understanding the Indian Economy\n2. edX - Economic Development in India\n\nDocumentaries:\n1. \"India Transformed\" (Economic reforms documentary)\n2. BBC documentaries on Indian economic development\n\nWebsites/Blogs:\n1. Business Standard\n2. Economic Times\n3. Mint\n4. Ideas for India (academic economic blog)\n\nThese resources provide diverse perspectives on India's economic evolution, reforms, challenges, and opportunities.",
